{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GyNZYa8zoCsSDdyaZkXM3f","type":"tool_result","content":"==PROMPT\nA 3-node Elasticsearch cluster is running.\n\nGoal:\n- Add two new data nodes with a different allocation attribute from the existing nodes.\n- Ensure shards for index \"app-data\" relocate onto the new nodes.\n- Keep the cluster healthy.\n\nConstraints:\n- Do not install operators or CRDs.\n\nVerification:\n1. Cluster health is yellow/green with 5 nodes.\n2. app-data shards are present on nodes outside the original 3.\n3. New nodes have a different allocation attribute than the original nodes.\n4. es-cluster StatefulSet remains at 3 replicas.\n==PRECON\n[precondition:es_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'es_env_ready':probe] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n6\n\n[precondition:nodeset_seed_fixture:preconditionUnits[1] 'nodeset_seed_fixture':probe] $ /bin/sh -c 'pw=$(kubectl -n elasticsearch get secret elastic-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null); A=\"\"; [ -n \"$pw\" ] && A=\"-u elastic:$pw\"; kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -sk $A --max-time 5 \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/app-data/_count\" 2>/dev/null | grep -q \"\\\"count\\\"\"'\n\n[precondition:nodeset_seed_fixture:preconditionUnits[1] 'nodeset_seed_fixture':apply] $ /bin/sh -c 'pw=$(kubectl -n elasticsearch get secret elastic-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null); A=\"\"; [ -n \"$pw\" ] && A=\"-u elastic:$pw\"; kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -sk $A -XPUT \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/app-data\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d \"{\\\"settings\\\":{\\\"number_of_shards\\\":3,\\\"number_of_replicas\\\":1}}\" >/dev/null 2>&1; kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -sk $A -XPOST \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/app-data/_doc/1\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d \"{\\\"msg\\\":\\\"alpha\\\"}\" >/dev/null 2>&1; kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -sk $A -XPOST \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/app-data/_doc/2\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d \"{\\\"msg\\\":\\\"beta\\\"}\" >/dev/null 2>&1; kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -sk $A -XPOST \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/app-data/_doc/3\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d \"{\\\"msg\\\":\\\"gamma\\\"}\" >/dev/null 2>&1; true'\n\n[precondition:nodeset_seed_fixture:preconditionUnits[1] 'nodeset_seed_fixture':verify] $ /bin/sh -c 'pw=$(kubectl -n elasticsearch get secret elastic-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null); A=\"\"; [ -n \"$pw\" ] && A=\"-u elastic:$pw\"; kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -sk $A --max-time 5 \"http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/app-data/_count\" >/dev/null 2>&1; true'\n\n\n==BUNDLE","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"666944db-1f25-46b3-a9c4-6c32d64fae85","uuid":"3616f70c-b243-44b3-95bc-7b4533058f69","timestamp":"2026-06-18T11:48:29.029Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"==PROMPT\nA 3-node Elasticsearch cluster is running.\n\nGoal:\n- Add two new data nodes with a different allocation attribute from the existing nodes.\n- Ensure shards for index \"app-data\" relocate onto the new nodes.\n- Keep the cluster healthy.\n\nConstraints:\n- Do not install operators or CRDs.\n\nVerification:\n1. Cluster health is yellow/green with 5 nodes.\n2. app-data shards are present on nodes outside the original 3.\n3. New nodes have a different allocation attribute than the original nodes.\n4. es-cluster StatefulSet remains at 3 replicas.\n==PRECON\n[precondition:es_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'es_env_ready':probe] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n6\n\n[precondition:nodeset_seed_fixture:preconditionUnits[1] 'nodeset_seed_fixture':probe] $ /bin/sh -c 'pw=$(kubectl -n elasticsearch get secret elastic-password -o jsonpath=\"{.da