{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01RBZsZG6m5rG9EBCuBHRY14","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. The task is complete and all four verification criteria are satisfied.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Goal:** Add two new data nodes with a different allocation attribute, relocate `app-data` shards onto them, keep the cluster healthy — without operators/CRDs.\n\n**What I did:**\n\n1. **New nodeset** — Created a *separate* StatefulSet `es-data-new` (2 replicas) joining the existing `es-cluster`, with its own headless Service and a ConfigMap. The new nodes:\n   - reuse the cluster's TLS and file-realm secrets,\n   - seed-discover `es-cluster-0/1/2`,\n   - run as `node.roles: [data, ingest]` (non-master, so quorum is untouched),\n   - carry allocation attribute **`node.attr.zone: new`** (the original 3 nodes have no zone attribute).\n\n2. **Shard relocation** — Set `index.routing.allocation.require.zone=new` on `app-data`; its shards moved onto `es-data-new-0/1`.\n\n3. **Cluster health fix** — The original `es-cluster` pods were stuck NotReady because their baked `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` env was stale versus the current `elastic-password` secret (readiness probe got 401). A `rollout restart` (replicas unchanged at 3) made them re-read the current secret and go Ready, restoring the `es-http` service endpoints.\n\n**Verification (via `es-http`):**\n| Check | Result |\n|---|---|\n| Health yellow/green, 5 nodes | ✅ green, `number_of_nodes=5` |\n| app-data shards outside original 3 | ✅ on `es-data-new-0/1` |\n| New nodes have a different allocation attr | ✅ `zone=new` (originals have none) |\n| es-cluster StatefulSet at 3 replicas | ✅ 3 |\n\nNote: `app-data` turned out to have a single shard (1 primary + 1 replica) in the live cluster, both of which relocated onto the two new nodes."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1308,"cache_read_input_to